HTMLElement.translate \- HTMLElement: translate property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]translate\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R] interface indicates whether an element\(cqs
attribute values and the values of its \f[CR]Text\f[R] node children are
to be translated when the page is localized, or whether to leave them
unchanged.
.PP
It reflects the value of the \f[CR]translate\f[R] HTML global attribute.
.SH VALUE
A boolean value that is \f[CR]true\f[R] if an element\(cqs attribute
values and the values of its \f[CR]Text\f[R] node children are to be
translated when the page is localized, \f[CR]false\f[R] otherwise.
